In [69]:
# Visualising Profit and Sales across states

csp = df.groupby("State")[["Sales","Profit"]].sum().sort_values(by = "Sales", ascending = False)
csp[:].plot.bar(color = ["orange","blue"],figsize = (18,8))
plt.title("Profit/Loss & Sales across States")
plt.xlabel("states")
plt.xlabel("Profit/Loss & Sales")
plt.show()
In [70]:
#Visualising Profit and Sales across different Categories
df.groupby("Category")[["Profit","Sales"]].sum().plot.bar(color = ["green","blue"],figsize = (8,5))
plt.ylabel("Profit /Loss and Sales")
plt.show()

Technology and Office Supplies Category have high sales with good profit and furniture has least profit.
